"Available"}, "features": {"large": {"faces": []}, "medium": {"faces": []}, "orig": {"faces": []}, "small": {"faces": []}}, "id_str": "2043094631030906880", "indices": [279, 302], "media_key": "3_2043094631030906880", "media_results": {"result": {"media_key": "3_2043094631030906880"}}, "media_url_https": "https://pbs.twimg.com/media/HFqHvf0a4AASvBj.jpg", "original_info": {"focus_rects": [{"h": 1147, "w": 2048, "x": 0, "y": 137}, {"h": 1284, "w": 1284, "x": 382, "y": 0}, {"h": 1284, "w": 1126, "x": 461, "y": 0}, {"h": 1284, "w": 642, "x": 703, "y": 0}, {"h": 1284, "w": 2048, "x": 0, "y": 0}], "height": 1284, "width": 2048}, "sizes": {"large": {"h": 1284, "resize": "fit", "w": 2048}, "medium": {"h": 752, "resize": "fit", "w": 1200}, "small": {"h": 426, "resize": "fit", "w": 680}, "thumb": {"h": 150, "resize": "crop", "w": 150}}, "type": "photo", "url": "https://t.co/EHtMowJVaz"}]}, "favorite_count": 0, "favorited": false, "full_text": "If a whistleblower with journalistic and photographic credentials is consistently documenting anomalies in the sky, could it be that they wanted me to be the one to advance the alien narrative? What they didn’t anticipate, however, was my deep dive into photonics—triggered by a https://t.co/EHtMowJVaz", "id_str": "2043094664207614322", "is_quote_status": false, "lang": "en", "possibly_sensitive": false, "possibly_sensitive_editable": true, "quote_count": 0, "reply_count": 2, "retweet_count": 0, "retweeted": false, "user_id_str": "24033053"}, "note_tweet": {"is_expandable": true, "note_tweet_results": {"result": {"entity_set": {"hashtags": [], "symbols": [], "urls": [], "user_mentions": []}, "id": "Tm90ZVR3ZWV0OjIwNDMwOTQ2NjQwOTg1MjUxODQ=", "text": "If a whistleblower with journalistic and photographic credentials is consistently documenting anomalies in the sky, could it be that they wanted me to be the one to advance the alien narrative? What they didn’t anticipate, however, was my deep dive into photonics—triggered by a land dispute with a photonics expert who holds a personal vendetta. To project light, there has to be a source. So, could the jet at the top right corner of this photo be the very source of that projection? And if so, is it possible that defense contractors are pushing the alien narrative by projecting these images? After all, who stands to benefit most from this story? Follow the money.  

Does it strike you as odd that the dark anomaly in the sky is almost dead center of the photo I shot of the Seattle skyline? It stands to reason, the projection was framed for my shot. 

Tonia Allen-Gould"}}}, "rest_id": "2043094664207614322", "source": "<a href="http://twitter.com/#!/download/ipad" rel="nofollow">Twitter for iPad</a>", "unmention_data": {}, "views": {"count": "30", "state": "EnabledWithCount"}}

text:
@aleabitoreddit The market seems to be in a photonics frenzy this year, and I've been following your posts since February.

Is there no foreseeable cooldown to this trend? 

Also, I get that there's a memory chip shortage, but SNDK is up 2,800% in 1 year. There is enough backlog to justify this?

